French buying power should remain stablethis year despite lower economic growth, while investment willrise sharply, Prime Minister Jacques Chirac said.    "I think we will maintain our buying power... I do not thinkit will fall," Chirac told a radio interviewer yesterday. Lastyear French household buying power rose 2.9 pct.    Chirac said economic growth would be substantially lowerthan originally forecast but investment would rise by close to16 pct in the 1986 to 1988 period, reversing the 3.8 pctdecline in the previous four-year period. REUTER&#3;